System Description
CabsOnline is a web-based taxi booking system that allows customers to register, login, and book taxi services online. The system includes an admin panel for managing bookings.

How to Use the System

For Customers:

1. New Customers â€“ Registration 
   - Visit: register.php
   - Fill in all required fields (Customer Name, Password, Re-type Password, Email, Phone)
   - Email must be unique in the system
   - Passwords must match
   - Upon successful registration, you will be redirected to the booking page

2. Existing Customers - Login
   - Visit: login.php
   - Enter your email address and password
   - Upon successful login, you will be redirected to the booking page

3. Making a Booking
   - Fill in all required fields on the booking page
   - Unit number is optional
   - Pick-up date/time must be at least 40 minutes from current time
   - You will receive a booking reference number and confirmation email

For Admin:

4. Admin Functions:
   - Visit: admin.php
   - List All: Shows unassigned bookings with pick-up time within next 2 hours
   - Assign: Enter booking reference number to assign a taxi to that booking

Files in the System

PHP Files:
- register.php - Customer registration page
- login.php - Customer login page  
- booking.php - Taxi booking form and processing
- admin.php - Admin panel for viewing and managing bookings




Database Files:
- database_setup.txt - MySQL commands to create required tables

Documentation:
- readme.doc - This file with system instructions
- Checklist-for-Project_1 - Task completion checklist

Database Tables

customer table:
- email (PRIMARY KEY)
- customer_name
- password (hashed)
- phone

booking table:
- booking_number (PRIMARY KEY)
- customer_email (FOREIGN KEY)
- passenger_name
- passenger_phone
- unit_number (nullable)
- street_number
- street_name
- suburb
- destination_suburb
- pickup_date
- pickup_time
- booking_datetime
- status (default: 'unassigned')

Technical Notes

- All passwords are hashed using PHP's password_hash() function
- Sessions are used to maintain user login state
- Email notifications are sent using PHP's mail() function
- Input validation and error handling implemented throughout
- SQL injection protection using prepared statements
- All pages display student ID in top-right corner

